{"word":"τρῖψις","slug":"τρῖψις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τρῖψις</b></el> <el>(τρῖψις, εως,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τρίβω'><el>τρίβω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>rubbing, friction</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>resistance to the touch when rubbed, firmness</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><el>τρίψεις</el> <i>potted meats</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}